  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2007-01-04",
    "date": "2007-01-23T21:18:18Z",
    "text": "Intelligence Community Audit Act of 2007 - Reaffirms the authority of the Comptroller General to audit and evaluate financial transactions, programs, and activities of elements of the intelligence community (those elements identified in the National Security Act of 1947) and obtain access to records for such purposes.\n\nAllows the Comptroller General to conduct an audit or evaluation of intelligence sources and methods or covert actions only upon a request of a congressional intelligence committee or the majority or minority leader of the Senate or the House of Representatives. Requires the Comptroller General to disclose the results of any such audit or evaluation only to the original requestor, the Director of National Intelligence, and the head of the relevant element of the intelligence community.\n\nRequires the Comptroller General to establish safeguards to protect the unauthorized disclosure of all classified and other sensitive information furnished to the Comptroller General in conducting an audit or evaluation.\n\nRequires elements of the intelligence community to cooperate with the Comptroller General in providing documentation and information necessary for audits and evaluations."
  },
